{{see|now you're cooking}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From the suggestion that [[stoves]] using [[natural gas]] as a [[fuel]] cook better or more efficiently than, for instance, wood burning or electric stoves.
===Idiom===
'''[[cooking]] [[with]] [[gas]]'''
#{{idiom}} A phrase meaning that the subject is now doing something the "right" way, or in the most powerful or efficient way. 
#:'' Once I switched to the new API, I was really '''cooking with gas'''.  I got the project done in half the time.  ''